The  Bank for International
Settlements  appointed U.S. Federal Reserve Bank of New York
President  William Dudley  to lead a committee on the global
financial system, replacing Bank of Canada Governor  Mark Carney .  The Basel, Switzerland-based BIS made the announcement on
its website today, and the change is effective immediately.   To contact the reporter on this story:
